goto project directory

git init

git status

git add .

git status

git commit -m "Initial commit"

git status

git remote add origin git@github.com:ravi-ghadiya/Document-management-system.git

git push origin master


if gives error for above command try with this:
git push origin master --force



To clone project in current directory
git clone <ssh-key of project>

--> to create build of project excluding test and javadoc
./gradlew clean build publishtomavenlocal -i -x test -x javadoc


pull from branch
git pull origin <branch-name>

git reset --hard


**********************************************************************************************************
to create new branch and checkut directly that branch
git checkout -b <branch-name>


to checkout another branch
git checkout <branch-name>

git status

to see code diff
git diff

git add --all

git commit -m "firmware update"

git push origin <branch-name>



--> go to particular project in GitLab and  Merge requests -> new merge request
--> add source and target branches (generally source  would be the new branch u have created and target would be development branch)
--> compare branches and continue -> uncheck delete branch checkbox -> merge

